<h3>DOCTORAL DEGREE PROGRAM IN COMPUTER ENGINEERING</h3>
<p>Doctoral degree program of Computer Engineering provides training and deepening of the theoretical and methodological knowledge and competence of doctoral students who can independently lead original and scientifically based research after graduation, and to critically evaluate the research of others.</p>
<h3>PROGRAM OBJECTIVES</h3>
<p>The doctoral degree program in Computer Engineering is a three-year program, which consists of courses and seminars. The program offers to students the following:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Development of creative skills in the interpretation and application of informatics principles and allow the acquisition of specific research skills in line with modern directions of development of information technologies</li>
  <li>Acquisition of specific knowledge in the field of computer engineering through software engineering, algorithm analysis, design of digital systems, advanced systems for database management, management information systems, network information system and methods of system design</li>
  <li>Acquirement of knowledge and development of academic skills for independent handling of the scientific research in a given area</li>
  <li>Participation in national and international scientific research projects</li>
  <li>Development of the ability to organize and participate in interdisciplinary and multidisciplinary research</li>
  <li>Training of candidates for independent use of scientific literature</li>
  <li>Creating conditions for a successful and responsible scientific work in accordance with the highest professional and ethical standards</li>
  <li>Students become skilled and specialized intellectuals, various employment opportunities are available to them, as well as personal development and training, and in the future we expect their significant contribution to the overall</li>
</ul>
